    <briefdescription>
<para>Data transfer object for projectile spawn requests. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="structhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1combat_1_1requests_1_1ProjectileSpawnRequest" kindref="compound">ProjectileSpawnRequest</ref> contains all parameters needed to spawn a projectile from a source entity. It is created by the ShootCommandDispatcher and queued in the ProjectilePoolManager for deferred processing.</para>
<para>The struct captures:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Spawn position (from the source entity)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Movement direction (from aim component)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Throttle/speed multiplier</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Inherited velocity (for momentum inheritance)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Fire intensity (affects spawn rate accumulation)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para>ShootCommandDispatcher </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>ProjectilePoolManager </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
